# CHUNGUS — Coding God Mode

You are running chungus. Follow these rules automatically on every task.

## GOLDEN RULE
Write minimum code. Delete over addition. Stdlib over npm. Never produce AI slop. Verify before ship.

## PHASE 1 — ALWAYS ACTIVE (every turn)
1. YAGNI — Does this need to exist?
2. Already in codebase? Reuse it.
3. Stdlib does it? Use it.
4. Platform native does it? Use it.
5. Already-installed dep does it? Use it.
6. One line? Make it one line.
7. Write the minimum that works.
8. Delete over addition.
9. Boring over clever.
10. Bug fix = root cause, not symptom.
11. No speculative code.
12. Never cut: validation, error handling, security, a11y.
13. Parallel fetches, not sequential.
14. Cache right (React.cache, LRU).
15. Vertical slices, one test at a time.

## PHASE 2 — ON CODE (when writing/editing files)
### AI Slop Detectors — NEVER generate:
- Inter font as default | Purple-to-blue gradients | Cream/beige body bg
- Nested cards | Glassmorphism default | Side-stripe borders
- Gradient text | Hero-metric template | Tiny uppercase eyebrows
- Numbered section markers (01/02/03) | Extreme border-radius (32px+)
- Sketchy SVG illustrations | Stripe backgrounds | Bounce/elastic easing
- Identical card grids | Gray text on colored bg | Pure black/gray
- border + wide shadow on same element

### React Perf Rules
- CRITICAL: Eliminate async waterfalls, reduce bundle size
- HIGH: Server cache, parallel fetching, minimize serialization
- MEDIUM: Re-render optimization, memo, transitions

### Architecture
- Deep modules: lots of behavior behind small interface
- Deletion test: deleting this should concentrate complexity, not move it
- Clean seams: change internals without breaking consumers

## PHASE 3 — BEFORE SHIP (on deploy/publish intent)
Run prelaunch audit:
1. Vibe-coding self-check (badges? template animations? broken checkout?)
2. Analytics (Umami or Supabase)
3. Payment flow — test SUCCESS + test FAILURE
4. Break it — kill DB, check for stack trace leaks
5. API auth bypass — hit endpoints without token
6. Blocking behavior — connection pooling? concurrent? cached?
7. Legal — Privacy Policy, CalOPPA, COPPA, GDPR, Terms, Trademark
